CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 2, 1955, pg. 11 reads: "Omega Wives - Charming wives of Omega Psi Phi men are planning gala doings to interest the wives and sweethearts of visiting fraters when they come to town April 15 to attend the regional meeting. Pictured, first row, Glading Avent and Madelyn Cole.  Second row: Roberta Watson, Jean Page, Eloise Brown, Dorothy  Conrad, Gertrude and Hazeltine Watkins.  Third row: Eunice Pittsman, Alberta Nelson, Mrs. Walter Parker and Rachel Brooks."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Omega Wives, from left, first row: Glading Avent and Madelyn Cole; second row: Roberta Watson, Jean Page, Eloise Robinson Brown, Dorothy  Conrad, Gertrude Watkins, and Hazeltine Watkins; third row: Eunice Pittsman, Alberta Nelson, Mrs. Walter Parker, and Rachel Brooks, posed in domestic interior with light colored sheer ruffled curtains, large radio, and lamp with ruffled shade
